"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-olympic-medals-paris-athletes-win-everything-to-know\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics have begun and athletes from around the world have begun to collect their hardware.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While winning an Olympic medal is historically significant any year, Olympic athletes who win a medal in 2024 get to take home a piece of one most famous structures in the history of the world.\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic glory is its own prize, but medals and money are pretty cool too.\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what Olympic medalists will earn by succeeding on the biggest stage in sports.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whenever the Eiffel Tower underwent renovations during the 20th century, pieces of the original wrough iron were preserved.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone in France probably wondered aloud why they did not throw that stuff away, but someone else probably kept saying they might use it for something someday.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998984988826395, \"rank\": 5.1967462288639836e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a victorious moment for that person when they decided to use that old metal for Olympic medals.\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According toThe Athletic, the gold medals, produced by French jeweler Chaumet, weigh 1.17 pounds, the silver medals weigh 1.16 pounds and the bronze comes in at an even pound.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9970585483263064, \"rank\": 0.002024274820495071, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Approximately 0.04 pounds of the Eiffel Tower iron is included in each medal.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theofficial Olympic website, the first eight athletes in each event \\\"receive a diploma, and their names are announced to the public.\\\"\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There does not appear to be a gift basket involved.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So all they get is a medal worth approximately $950according to Forbes.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.193033590893217e-15, \"text\": \"Forbes\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Forbes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic glory is great, but you can not pay your bills with prestige.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, home countries often give medalists with monetary rewards.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Olympians get$37,500 for a gold medal, $22,500 for a silver medal and $15,000 for a bronze.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other countries who win significantly fewer medals pay much more.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia, for example, isreportedly giving gold medalists$214,900 in 2024.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9996484650423595, \"rank\": 0.00020075350512450892, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malaysia and Morocco will also pay out over $200,000 to anyone who comes home with gold.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"score\": 0.999956170299479, \"rank\": 4.3769380391030856e-05, \"text\": \"Malaysia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9999908921932763, \"rank\": 4.69341377315828e-06, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to that, track athletes who win gold get an extra $50,000 from World Athletics.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999826209206, \"rank\": 1.7379216829003337e-08, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No matter how much you earn, you have always got a piece of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals have been given since the first modern Olympic games in 1896 in Athens, Greece.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8695314883090911, \"rank\": 0.15004460817480236, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2089, \"end\": 2095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999529987720937, \"rank\": 0.00045581974282933395, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theofficial Olympics website, first place was actually awarded a silver medal, an olive branch and a diploma.\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Second place got the only other medal which was a bronze-copper combination, a branch of laurel and a diploma.\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2309, \"end\": 2315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\", \"score\": 0.9999242878789466, \"rank\": 7.571785370376556e-05, \"text\": \"laurel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurel_wreath\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the games were played inParis four years laterfirst place received gilt silver, which is a silver gilded with gold.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Gilt silver and gold have been interchangeable ever since.)\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Second place got regular silver and third place earned bronze.\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh, and the medals were rectangular.\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What we think of as the traditional modern medal was debuted in1904 at the St. Louis Olympics.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold, silver and bronze were given to first, second and third place and the medals came attached to a colored ribbon.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Stephen Douglas is a Senior Writer on the Breaking & Trending News Team at Sports Illustrated.\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_A._Douglas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.837617593290927e-22, \"text\": \"Stephen Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_A._Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_A._Douglas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been in journalism and media since 2008, and now casts a wide net with coverage across all sports.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen spent more than a decade with The Big Lead and has previously written for Uproxx and The Sporting News.\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3203, \"end\": 3209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uproxx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.4546330201046e-25, \"text\": \"Uproxx\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uproxx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uproxx\"}, {\"begin\": 3218, \"end\": 3231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sporting_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.033244216827417e-16, \"text\": \"Sporting News\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sporting_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"h